modules.description: This module handles reading from and writing to tar archives using Unix file descriptors. It provides functions to extract files from and create tar archives, fold over archive entries, append files, and manipulate headers with support for extended attributes and compatibility levels. Concrete use cases include building or unpacking tarballs with selective filtering, validating tar headers, and appending files to existing archives.

This module handles reading from and writing to tar archives using Lwt_unix file descriptors. It provides functions to decode tar streams, fold over archive entries, extract files, create archives, and manipulate headers with support for extended attributes. Concrete use cases include extracting specific files from a tar archive, streaming tar data asynchronously, and building custom tar archives with filtering and compatibility options.
